hwDhcpProxy.name: hwDhcpProxy

revisions.description: V3.39, Modified the value range and description of hwDhcpSmltOption60.
V3.38, added hwDhcpDomainGatewayLearn, hwDhcpDomainGateway2 and hwDhcpDomainGateway3.
V3.37, Modified the value range of hwDhcpUserFlowID, hwDhcpSmltServicePortId and hwDhcpFlowStatisticsIndex.
V3.36, added the hwDhcpReverse.
V3.35, modified the version of MIB.
V3.34, modified the description of hwDhcpFlowStatisticsEntry.
V3.33, add hwDhcpFlowStatisticsTable for dhcp packet statistics on flow.

V3.32, modified the description of hwDhcpSecurityTable, hwDhcpPortPvcTable, hwDhcpPortTable, hwDhcpSuboptionTable, hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsEntry, hwDhcpClientProperty and hwDhcpClientSystemAutoConfigStatus.
V3.31, added rebuild(4) to hwDhcpOption82Status.
V3.30, modified the description.
V3.29, modified the value range of hwDhcpSmltOption60 and hwDhcpSmltDnsServerName.
V3.28, modified description of all leaves.
V3.27, added hwDhcpProxyVbOids and hwDhcpSmltResultTrap. Modified description of MIB file. Modified the value range of leaves.
V3.26, changed hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOverLenght to hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOverLength, hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveOverLenght to hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveOverLength.
V3.25, added table hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsTable for dhcp packet statistics.
V3.24, modified description of MIB file.
V3.22, changed SMI to SMIv2 standard.
V3.21, added value node hwSystemAutoConfigStatus for GE auto-config switch configuration.
V3.20, added table hwDhcpSmltTable for DHCP simulation.
V1.0, added DHCP Suboption

hwDhcpProxy.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwDhcpProxy.description: The MIB is used for defining Huawei's DHCP attribute. It includes DHCP L3 Relay, DHCP Proxy, DHCP Option82, DHCP User Log, and DHCP Simulation.

hwDhcpGroupTable.name: hwDhcpGroupTable
hwDhcpGroupTable.description: Describes the DHCP server group, including IP addresses of the primary DHCP server and secondary server in each group. It supports the create, modify, delete, and query operations. The index of this table is hwDhcpGroupID.

hwDhcpGroupEntry.name: hwDhcpGroupEntry
hwDhcpGroupEntry.description: Describes the DHCP server group, including IP addresses of the primary DHCP server and secondary server in each group. It supports the create, modify, delete, and query operations. The index of this entry is hwDhcpGroupID.

hwDhcpGroupID.name: hwDhcpGroupID
hwDhcpGroupID.description: Indicates the index of the DHCP server group. Range: 0C19

hwIpDhcpServerAddress1.name: hwIpDhcpServerAddress1
hwIpDhcpServerAddress1.description: Indicates the IP address of the first server in the DHCP server group. It must be a valid unicast IP address and must be different from existing IP addresses in other server groups.

hwIpDhcpServerAddress2.name: hwIpDhcpServerAddress2
hwIpDhcpServerAddress2.description: Indicates the IP address of the second server in the DHCP server group. It must be a valid unicast IP address, must be different from existing IP addresses in other server groups, and must be different from hwIpDhcpServerAddress1. When hwIpDhcpServerAddress1 is not configured, hwIpDhcpServerAddress2 cannot be configured.

hwDhcpRowStatus.name: hwDhcpRowStatus
hwDhcpRowStatus.description: Row status, used for configuring the DHCP server group. Options: 1. active(1) -when this leaf is queried, the value is fixed to active(1). 2. createAndGo(4) -create a DHCP server group 3. destroy(6) -delete a DHCP server group To create a DHCP server group, specify the index and leaf hwIpDhcpServerAddress1 (other leaves are optional), set hwDhcpRowStatus to createAndGo, and perform the set operation. To modify a DHCP server group, specify the index and leaf hwIpDhcpServerAddress1 (other leaves are optional) and perform the set operation. To delete a DHCP server group, specify index hwDhcpGroupID, set hwDhcpRowStatus to destroy(6), and perform the set operation. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1).

hwIpDhcpCurrentServerAddress.name: hwIpDhcpCurrentServerAddress
hwIpDhcpCurrentServerAddress.description: Indicates the IP address of the current server in the DHCP server group. It is a read-only leaf and is meaningful only when the DHCP server works in the backup mode. If the server does not work in the backup mode, it is 0.0.0.0 by default.

hwIpDhcpServerAddress3.name: hwIpDhcpServerAddress3
hwIpDhcpServerAddress3.description: Indicates the IP address of the third server in the DHCP server group. It must be a valid unicast IP address, must be different from existing IP addresses in other server groups, and must be different from hwIpDhcpServerAddress1 or hwIpDhcpServerAddress2. When hwIpDhcpServerAddress1 and hwIpDhcpServerAddress2 are not configured, hwIpDhcpServerAddress3 cannot be configured.

hwIpDhcpServerAddress4.name: hwIpDhcpServerAddress4
hwIpDhcpServerAddress4.description: Indicates the IP address of the fourth server in the DHCP server group. It must be a valid unicast IP address, must be different from existing IP addresses in other server groups, and must be different from hwIpDhcpServerAddress1, hwIpDhcpServerAddress2, or hwIpDhcpServerAddress3. When hwIpDhcpServerAddress1, hwIpDhcpServerAddress2, and hwIpDhcpServerAddress3 are not configured, hwIpDhcpServerAddress4 cannot be configured.

hwDhcpSecurityTable.name: hwDhcpSecurityTable
hwDhcpSecurityTable.description: A table containing the information of dhcp security. If security feature is supported by DHCP, add/delete table item of the user address, whose IP is the index. dhcp relay records in the table the IP address and MAC address of the legal user who acquire the IP address through relay. Through this table, the information of legal users can be queried. Moreover, in order to meet the needs of users to configure fixed IP address. This table enables the information configuration of the legal user with a fixed IP address. Specify the IP address, MAC address and the property of the static/dynamic address to implement the create operation. The index of this table is hwDhcpClientIpAddress.

hwDhcpSecurityEntry.name: hwDhcpSecurityEntry
hwDhcpSecurityEntry.description: A table containing the information of dhcp security. If security feature is supported by DHCP, add/delete table item of the user address, whose IP is the index. dhcp relay records in the table the IP address and MAC address of the legal user who acquire the IP address through relay. Through this table, the information of legal users can be queried. Moreover, in order to meet the needs of users to configure fixed IP address. This table enables the information configuration of the legal user with a fixed IP address. Specify the IP address, MAC address and the property of the static/dynamic address to implement the create operation. The index of this entry is hwDhcpClientIpAddress.

hwDhcpClientProperty.name: hwDhcpClientProperty
hwDhcpClientProperty.description: Property of client. Options: 1. static(1) -indicates client property is static 2. dynamic(2) -indicates client property is dynamic

hwDhcpToL3IfTable.name: hwDhcpToL3IfTable
hwDhcpToL3IfTable.description: Describes the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group. It supports the create, query, and modify operations. The index of this table is hwDhcpToL3VlanIfIndex.

hwDhcpToL3IfEntry.name: hwDhcpToL3IfEntry
hwDhcpToL3IfEntry.description: Describes the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group. It supports the create, query, and modify operations. The index of this entry is hwDhcpToL3VlanIfIndex.

hwDhcpToL3VlanIfIndex.name: hwDhcpToL3VlanIfIndex
hwDhcpToL3VlanIfIndex.description: Indicates binding to the VLAN ID of the DHCP server group. It uses hwVlanInterfaceID of hwVlanInterfaceTable. Range: 1C4093

hwDhcpToL3GroupId.name: hwDhcpToL3GroupId
hwDhcpToL3GroupId.description: Indicates the corresponding DHCP server group of the VLAN interface. Range: 0-20 In the configuration, if the value of hwDhcpToL3GroupId is in the range of 0C19, ensure that the server group corresponding to this ID exists. Value 20 of hwDhcpToL3GroupId indicates unbinding. In the query, if this interface is not bound to any server group, value 20 of hwDhcpToL3GroupId is returned.

hwDhcpToL3AddressCheck.name: hwDhcpToL3AddressCheck
hwDhcpToL3AddressCheck.description: If dhcp security check enabled for this vlan virtual interface. By default, it is disabled. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates dhcp security check is enabled 2. disabled(2) -indicates dhcp security check is disabled

hwDhcpToL3RowStatus.name: hwDhcpToL3RowStatus
hwDhcpToL3RowStatus.description: Indicates the row status, used to configure the corresponding DHCP server group of the VLAN interface. Options: 1. active(1) -when this leaf is queried, the value is fixed to active(1). 2. createAndGo(4) -create a binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group 3. destroy(6) -delete a binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group Creates the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group. Specify the index and hwDhcpToL3GroupId, set hwDhcpToL3RowStatus to createAndGo(4), and perform the set operation. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1). Modifies the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group. Specify the index and hwDhcpToL3GroupId, set hwDhcpToL3RowStatus to active(1), and perform the set operation. Value 20 of hwDhcpToL3GroupId indicates unbinding. Deletes the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group, Specify the index and hwDhcpToL3GroupId, set hwDhcpToL3RowStatus to destroy(6), and perform the set operation.

hwDhcpPortPvcTable.name: hwDhcpPortPvcTable
hwDhcpPortPvcTable.description: Indicates DHCP pvc supported port management feature. The indexes of this table are ifIndex, hwAdsllinePvcVpi and hwAdslLinePvcVci.

hwDhcpPortPvcEntry.name: hwDhcpPortPvcEntry
hwDhcpPortPvcEntry.description: Indicates DHCP pvc supported port management feature. The indexes of this entry are ifIndex, hwAdsllinePvcVpi and hwAdslLinePvcVci.

hwDhcpPortPvcOption82AdminStatus.name: hwDhcpPortPvcOption82AdminStatus
hwDhcpPortPvcOption82AdminStatus.description: DHCP Option82 on pvc of port administer state: true(enable)/false(disable),the default is false. Options: 1. true(1) -indicates DHCP Option82 is on 2. false(2) -indicates DHCP Option82 is off

hwDhcpPortPvcIPBindAdminStatus.name: hwDhcpPortPvcIPBindAdminStatus
hwDhcpPortPvcIPBindAdminStatus.description: IP Binding on pvc of port administer state: true(enable)/false(disable),the default is false. Options: 1. true(1) -indicates IP Binding is enabled 2. false(2) -indicates IP Binding is disabled

hwDhcpPortPvcRowStatus.name: hwDhcpPortPvcRowStatus
hwDhcpPortPvcRowStatus.description: Row status. Add or delete a table item. Options: 1. active(1) -indicates query operation 2. createAndGo(4) -indicates creating operation 3. destroy(6) -indicates deleting operation

hwDhcpPortTable.name: hwDhcpPortTable
hwDhcpPortTable.description: Indicates DHCP port management feature. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwDhcpPortEntry.name: hwDhcpPortEntry
hwDhcpPortEntry.description: Indicates DHCP port management feature. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwDhcpPortOption82AdminStatus.name: hwDhcpPortOption82AdminStatus
hwDhcpPortOption82AdminStatus.description: DHCP Option82 on port administer state: true(enable)/false(disable),the default is false. Options: 1. true(1) -indicates DHCP Option82 is on 2. false(2) -indicates DHCP Option82 is off

hwDhcpPortUpLinkStatus.name: hwDhcpPortUpLinkStatus
hwDhcpPortUpLinkStatus.description: Up-link administer state, only a port on main board can be an up-link; true(yes)/false(no),the default is true. Options: 1. true(1) -indicates only a port on main board can be an up-link 2. false(2) -indicates not only a port on main board can be an up-link

hwDhcpPortRowStatus.name: hwDhcpPortRowStatus
hwDhcpPortRowStatus.description: Row status. Add or delete a table item.

hwDhcpDomainTable.name: hwDhcpDomainTable
hwDhcpDomainTable.description: Describes the DHCP domain information in the DHCP option 60 mode. It supports the query, create, modify, and delete operations. The index of this table is hwDhcpDomainName.

hwDhcpDomainEntry.name: hwDhcpDomainEntry
hwDhcpDomainEntry.description: Describes the DHCP domain information in the DHCP option 60 mode. It supports the query, create, modify, and delete operations. The index of this entry is hwDhcpDomainName.

hwDhcpDomainName.name: hwDhcpDomainName
hwDhcpDomainName.description: Indicates the DHCP domain name, which is used with the option 60 field in the user packets to differentiate various types of users in DHCP option 60 mode. Range: 1C32 characters The format is character string length+character ASCII length. For example, the length of 'hwdomain' is 8 and its corresponding octet string is 8.104.119.100.111.109.97.105.110.

hwDhcpDomainGroupId.name: hwDhcpDomainGroupId
hwDhcpDomainGroupId.description: Indicates the corresponding DHCP server group of the domain. It uses hwDhcpGroupID in hwDhcpGroupTable. Range: 0C20 0C19 indicates the ID of the server group; 20 indicates not binding with any server group.

hwDhcpDomainRowStatus.name: hwDhcpDomainRowStatus
hwDhcpDomainRowStatus.description: Row status, used for configuring the DHCP domain name. Options: 1. active(1) -when this leaf is queried, the value is fixed to active(1). 2. createAndGo(4) -create a DHCP domain name 3. destroy(6) -delete a DHCP domain name Create a DHCP domain name, specify hwDhcpDomainName as the index, set hwDhcpDomainRowStatus to createAndGo(4), and perform the set operation. hwDhcpDomainGroupId is used to bind to a domain name or a DHCP server group. It is an optional leaf. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1). When modifying or configuring hwDhcpDomainGroupId, specify hwDhcpDomainName and hwDhcpDomainGroupId and perform the set operation. When deleting a DHCP domain name, specify hwDhcpDomainName, set hwDhcpDomainRowStatus to destroy(6), and perform the set operation.

hwDhcpDomainGatewayLearn.name: hwDhcpDomainGatewayLearn
hwDhcpDomainGatewayLearn.description: Indicates the function of automatically learning the relay IP addresses of the DHCP packets that belong to this domain. Data type:INTEGER Options: 1. enable(1) -enable the IP address learning function for the DHCP gateway 2. disable(2) -disable the IP address learning function for the DHCP gateway Access right: read-write Default: disable(2)

hwDhcpMacRangeTable.name: hwDhcpMacRangeTable
hwDhcpMacRangeTable.description: Describes the DHCP MAC-range information in the DHCP MAC-range mode. It supports the query, create, modify, and delete operations. The index of this table is hwDhcpMacRangeName.

hwDhcpMacRangeEntry.name: hwDhcpMacRangeEntry
hwDhcpMacRangeEntry.description: Describes the DHCP MAC-range information in the DHCP MAC-range mode. It supports the query, create, modify, and delete operations. The index of this entry is hwDhcpMacRangeName.

hwDhcpMacRangeName.name: hwDhcpMacRangeName
hwDhcpMacRangeName.description: DHCP MAC-range, used with the user MAC addresses to differentiate various types of users in DHCP MAC-range mode. Range: 1C32 characters For example, the index of 'mran' is 4.109.114.97.110.

hwDhcpMacRangeStart.name: hwDhcpMacRangeStart
hwDhcpMacRangeStart.description: Indicates the start address of the MAC-range, which must be a valid unicast MAC address. The format is a 6-byte hexadecimal character string, for example, 0x00 0xe0 0xfc 0x11 0x00 0x00.

hwDhcpMacRangeEnd.name: hwDhcpMacRangeEnd
hwDhcpMacRangeEnd.description: Indicates the end address of the MAC-range, which must be a valid unicast MAC address. hwDhcpMacRangeEnd must be equal to or larger than hwDhcpMacRangeStart. The format is a 6-byte hexadecimal character string, for example, 0x00 0xe0 0xfc 0x11 0x00 0x00.

hwDhcpMacRangeGroupId.name: hwDhcpMacRangeGroupId
hwDhcpMacRangeGroupId.description: Indicates the DHCP server group relevant to the MAC-range.

hwDhcpMacRangeRowStatus.name: hwDhcpMacRangeRowStatus
hwDhcpMacRangeRowStatus.description: Row status, used to create a MAC-range, modify a MAC-range, and bind a MAC-range to a DHCP server group. Options: 1. active(1) -in the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1). 2. createAndGo(4) -create a MAC-range to a DHCP server group 3. destroy(6) -delete a MAC-range to a DHCP server group To create a MAC-range, hwDhcpMacRangeName must be specified. At the same time, hwDhcpMacRangeStart and hwDhcpMacRangeEnd can be selected and configured. In addition, hwDhcpMacRangeGroupId can also be configured. Finally, set hwDhcpMacRangeRowStatus to createAndGo(4) and perform the set operation. The restrictions on the modify and create operations are the same, but the row status need not be bound. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1). In the delete operation, hwDhcpMacRangeName needs to be specified. Set hwDhcpDomainRowStatus to destroy(6) and perform the set operation.

hwDhcpDomainGatewayTable.name: hwDhcpDomainGatewayTable
hwDhcpDomainGatewayTable.description: Describes the binding between the DHCP domain and gateway corresponding to the VLAN interface in the DHCP option 60 mode. It supports the modify and query operations. The indexes of this table are hwDhcpDomainGatewayVlanIfIndex and hwDhcpDomainGatewayDmName.

hwDhcpDomainGatewayEntry.name: hwDhcpDomainGatewayEntry
hwDhcpDomainGatewayEntry.description: Describes the binding between the DHCP domain and gateway corresponding to the VLAN interface in the DHCP option 60 mode. It supports the modify and query operations. The indexes of this entry are hwDhcpDomainGatewayVlanIfIndex and hwDhcpDomainGatewayDmName.

hwDhcpDomainGatewayVlanIfIndex.name: hwDhcpDomainGatewayVlanIfIndex
hwDhcpDomainGatewayVlanIfIndex.description: Indicates the VLAN ID to be bound to the gateway. Range: 1C4093

hwDhcpDomainGatewayDmName.name: hwDhcpDomainGatewayDmName
hwDhcpDomainGatewayDmName.description: DHCP domain name. Range: 1C32 characters The format is character string length+character ASCII length. For example, the length of 'hwdomain' is 8 and its corresponding octet string is 8.104.119.100.111.109.97.105.110.

hwDhcpDomainGateway.name: hwDhcpDomainGateway
hwDhcpDomainGateway.description: Indicates the gateway IP address bound to the VLAN interface in the DHCP domain.

hwDhcpDomainGatewayRowStatus.name: hwDhcpDomainGatewayRowStatus
hwDhcpDomainGatewayRowStatus.description: Row status, used for binding a VLAN interface to a DHCP domain or gateway. Options: 1. active(1) -indicates query operation When modifying the binding between the DHCP domain and the gateway, configure hwDhcpDomainGateway to the gateway IP address to be bound to. Make sure that the IP address exists under the interface, and it can be the primary or secondary IP address of the interface. If the value is 0.0.0.0, it indicates that no gateway is bound to. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1).

hwDhcpDomainGateway2.name: hwDhcpDomainGateway2
hwDhcpDomainGateway2.description: Indicates the second gateway IP address bound to the VLAN interface in the DHCP domain.

hwDhcpDomainGateway3.name: hwDhcpDomainGateway3
hwDhcpDomainGateway3.description: Indicates the third gateway IP address bound to the VLAN interface in the DHCP domain.

hwDhcpMacGatewayTable.name: hwDhcpMacGatewayTable
hwDhcpMacGatewayTable.description: Describes the binding between the VLAN interface and the gateway in the DHCP MAC-range mode. It supports the query and modify operations. The indexes of this table are hwDhcpMacGatewayVlanIfIndex and hwDhcpMacGatewayMacName.

hwDhcpMacGatewayEntry.name: hwDhcpMacGatewayEntry
hwDhcpMacGatewayEntry.description: Describes the binding between the VLAN interface and the gateway in the DHCP MAC-range mode. It supports the query and modify operations. The indexes of this entry are hwDhcpMacGatewayVlanIfIndex and hwDhcpMacGatewayMacName.

hwDhcpMacGatewayVlanIfIndex.name: hwDhcpMacGatewayVlanIfIndex
hwDhcpMacGatewayVlanIfIndex.description: Indicates the VLAN ID to be bound to. Range: 1C4093

hwDhcpMacGatewayMacName.name: hwDhcpMacGatewayMacName
hwDhcpMacGatewayMacName.description: Indicates the name of the DHCP MAC-range. It uses hwDhcpMacRangeName in hwDhcpMacRangeTable. Range: 1C32 characters

hwDhcpMacGateway.name: hwDhcpMacGateway
hwDhcpMacGateway.description: Indicates the gateway IP address bound to the VLAN interface in the DHCP MAC-range. It uses hwVlanIpAddress (primary IP address) in hwVlanInterfaceTable. Make sure that the IP address exists under the interface, and it can be the primary or secondary IP address of the interface. If the value is 0.0.0.0, it indicates that no gateway is bound to.

hwDhcpMacGatewayRowStatus.name: hwDhcpMacGatewayRowStatus
hwDhcpMacGatewayRowStatus.description: Row status, used to bind a MAC-range to the gateway IP address. In the modify operation, specify hwDhcpMacGateway and perform the set operation. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1). Options: 1. active(1) -in the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1).

hwDhcpOption82StatisticsTable.name: hwDhcpOption82StatisticsTable
hwDhcpOption82StatisticsTable.description: Describes the statistics of various DHCP packets received on the DHCP L2 relay. It supports the query and set operations. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwDhcpOption82StatisticsEntry.name: hwDhcpOption82StatisticsEntry
hwDhcpOption82StatisticsEntry.description: Describes the statistics of various DHCP packets received on the DHCP L2 relay. It supports the query and set operations. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveUntrust.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveUntrust
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveUntrust.description: Indicates the total number of DHCP packets containing the untrust option 82 information. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOverLength.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOverLength
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOverLength.description: Indicates the total number of DHCP packets that exceed the maximum packet length after option 82 is added. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveDiscover.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveDiscover
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveDiscover.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP discover packets. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOffer.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOffer
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOffer.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP offer packets. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveRequest.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveRequest
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveRequest.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP request packets. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveDecline.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveDecline
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveDecline.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP decline packets. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveAck.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveAck
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveAck.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP ACK packets. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveNak.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveNak
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveNak.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP NAK packets. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveRelease.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveRelease
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveRelease.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP release packets. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveInform.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveInform
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveInform.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP inform packets. Range: 0-4294967295

hwDhcpOption82StatisticsClear.name: hwDhcpOption82StatisticsClear
hwDhcpOption82StatisticsClear.description: Resets the statistics of DHCP packets. Set it to clear(1) and perform the set operation. Options: 1. clear(1) -resets the statistics of DHCP packets

hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOverMaxOption82Size.name: hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOverMaxOption82Size
hwDhcpOption82ReceiveOverMaxOption82Size.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP packets that exceed the maximum option 82 length after the option 82 information is added.

hwDhcpOption82Status.name: hwDhcpOption82Status
hwDhcpOption82Status.description: Indicates the status of the global DHCP Option82 switch. Options: 1. enable(1) -indicates adding a vendor tag to or deleting it from the DHCP packet on the device. 2. disable(2) -indicates not adding a vendor tag to or deleting it from the DHCP packet on the device. 3. forward(3) -indicates not processing the vendor tag of the DHCP packet. In this case, the packet is transparently transmitted. 4. rebuild(4) -indicates rebuild the vendor tag from the ONU device,to meet the TR-156 needs. Default: disable(2)

hwDhcpRelayMode.name: hwDhcpRelayMode
hwDhcpRelayMode.description: Describes the current DHCP forwarding mode of the system. Options: 1. layer2(3) -indicates L2 mode 2. layer3(1) -indicates L3 mode Default: layer2(3)

hwDhcpServerSelectMode.name: hwDhcpServerSelectMode
hwDhcpServerSelectMode.description: Describes the global DHCP server selection mode in the DHCP L3 relay mode. Currently, there are three modes: standard mode, option 60 mode, and MAC-range mode. Options: 1. standard(1) -indicates the standard mode 2. option60(2) -indicates the domain mode 3. macRange(3) -indicates the MAC-range mode Default: standard(1)

hwDhcpMaxLenAppendOp82.name: hwDhcpMaxLenAppendOp82
hwDhcpMaxLenAppendOp82.description: Indicates the allowable maximum length of a DHCP packet. Range: 500-1500 Unit: byte Default: 1500 bytes

hwDhcpCIDState.name: hwDhcpCIDState
hwDhcpCIDState.description: Circuit-id writing state,true(writing to DHCP packet)/false(not writing to DHCP packet). Default: true(1)

hwDhcpRIDState.name: hwDhcpRIDState
hwDhcpRIDState.description: Remote-id writing state,true(writing to DHCP packet)/false(not writing to DHCP packet). Default: true(1)

hwDhcpSuboption90Status.name: hwDhcpSuboption90Status
hwDhcpSuboption90Status.description: Indicates the status of Suboption90 of DHCP Option82. Options: 1. enable(1) -enable Suboption90 of DHCP Option82 2. disable(2) -disable Suboption90 of DHCP Option82 Default: disable(2)

hwDhcpRelayServerMode.name: hwDhcpRelayServerMode
hwDhcpRelayServerMode.description: Configures the working mode of the DHCP server. Options: 1. shareload(1) -indicates the load balancing mode. In this mode, the system forwards all DHCP packets from the user to all servers in the DHCP server group. 2. backup(2) -indicates the backup mode. In this mode, the system forwards packets from the user to only the primary server in the DHCP server group. When the primary server is disconnected, the packets are forwarded to the secondary server. Default: shareload(1)

hwDhcpServerReplyMaxTime.name: hwDhcpServerReplyMaxTime
hwDhcpServerReplyMaxTime.description: Configures or queries the response timeout time of packets of the DHCP server when the server works in the backup mode. Range: 1C60 Unit: second Default: 1

hwDhcpServerReplyOvertimeMaxTimes.name: hwDhcpServerReplyOvertimeMaxTimes
hwDhcpServerReplyOvertimeMaxTimes.description: Configures or queries the response timeout times of packets of the DHCP server when the server works in the backup mode. Range: 1C255 Default: 1

hwDhcpSuboptionTable.name: hwDhcpSuboptionTable
hwDhcpSuboptionTable.description: Indicates DHCP suboption feature. The index of this table is hwDhcpSuboptionIndex.

hwDhcpSuboptionEntry.name: hwDhcpSuboptionEntry
hwDhcpSuboptionEntry.description: Indicates DHCP suboption feature. The index of this entry is hwDhcpSuboptionIndex.

hwDhcpSuboptionIndex.name: hwDhcpSuboptionIndex
hwDhcpSuboptionIndex.description: The index of DHCP suboption: index 1 stand for suboption 0x81; index 2 stand for suboption 0x82; index 3 stand for suboption 0x83; index 4 stand for suboption 0x84; index 5 stand for suboption 0x85; index 6 stand for suboption 0x86; index 7 stand for suboption 0x87; index 8 stand for suboption 0x88; index 9 stand for suboption 0x89; index 10 stand for suboption 0x8a; index 11 stand for suboption 0x8b; index 12 stand for suboption 0x8c; index 13 stand for suboption 0x8d; index 14 stand for suboption 0x8e; index 15 stand for suboption 0x90;

hwDhcpSuboptionStatus.name: hwDhcpSuboptionStatus
hwDhcpSuboptionStatus.description: The configuration of DHCP suboption: true(enable)/false(disable),the default is false.. hwDhcpSuboptionStatus OBJECT-TYPE

hwDhcpSuboption7Status.name: hwDhcpSuboption7Status
hwDhcpSuboption7Status.description: Indicates the status of Suboption7 of DHCP Option82. Options: 1. enable(1) -indicates the Suboption7 of DHCP Option82 is enabled 2. disable(2) -indicates the Suboption7 of DHCP Option82 is disabled Default: disable(2)

hwDhcpProxyStatus.name: hwDhcpProxyStatus
hwDhcpProxyStatus.description: Describes the current status of the DHCP proxy switch. Options: 1. enable(1) -enable DHCP proxy 2. disable(2) -disable DHCP proxy Default: disable(2) Perform the query and modify operations through get and set operations.

hwDhcpLeaseTime.name: hwDhcpLeaseTime
hwDhcpLeaseTime.description: Describes the DHCP proxy lease time of the system. Range: 0, 300-10080 Unit: minute Default: 0 indicates that the lease time is not set. Perform the query and modify operations through get and set operations.

hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanTable.name: hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanTable
hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanTable.description: Describes the DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN and supports the query and modify operations. The index of this table is hwVlanIndex.

hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanEntry.name: hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanEntry
hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanEntry.description: Describes the DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN and supports the query and modify operations. The index of this entry is hwVlanIndex.

hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlan.name: hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlan
hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlan.description: Indicates the DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN interface. Options: 1. standard(1) -indicates the standard mode 2. option60(2) -indicates the domain mode 3. macRange(3) -indicates the MAC-range mode Default: standard(1)

hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanRowStatus.name: hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanRowStatus
hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanRowStatus.description: Row status, used to set the DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN interface. Options: 1. active(1) -when this leaf is queried, the value is fixed to active(1). 2. createAndGo(4) -create a DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN interface 3. destroy(6) -delete a DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN interface To create the DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN interface, bind to hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlan, set hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanRowStatus to createAndGo, and then perform the set operation. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1). To modify the DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN interface, specify hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlan and perform the set operation. To delete the DHCP server selection mode of the VLAN interface and use the global selection mode, specify hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlan, set hwDhcpServerSelectModeByVlanRowStatus to destroy(6), and perform the set operation.

hwDhcpUserTable.name: hwDhcpUserTable
hwDhcpUserTable.description: Provides the function of DHCP proxy user management, including querying the user information and forcing a user to go offline. The index of this table is hwDhcpUserIndex.

hwDhcpUserEntry.name: hwDhcpUserEntry
hwDhcpUserEntry.description: Provides the function of DHCP proxy user management, including querying the user information and forcing a user to go offline. The index of this entry is hwDhcpUserIndex.

hwDhcpUserIndex.name: hwDhcpUserIndex
hwDhcpUserIndex.description: Indicates the DHCP proxy user index. Range: 0-4095

hwDhcpUserPortIndex.name: hwDhcpUserPortIndex
hwDhcpUserPortIndex.description: Indicates the index of the port where the DHCP user resides. Its algorithm and value are the same as ifIndex.

hwDhcpUserFlowID.name: hwDhcpUserFlowID
hwDhcpUserFlowID.description: Indicates the ID of the service where the DHCP user resides. Here it indicates the service port ID created by the current device. The service port index on the NMS is 1 larger than the service port index on the host.

hwDhcpUserVlanID.name: hwDhcpUserVlanID
hwDhcpUserVlanID.description: Indicates the DHCP user VLAN index. Range: 1-4093

hwDhcpUserIpAddress.name: hwDhcpUserIpAddress
hwDhcpUserIpAddress.description: Indicates the IP address of the DHCP user dynamically obtained from the DHCP server, in dotted decimal notation, for example, 10.11.104.10.

hwDhcpUserMACAddress.name: hwDhcpUserMACAddress
hwDhcpUserMACAddress.description: Indicates the MAC address of the DHCP user. The format is a 6-byte hexadecimal character string, for example, 0x00 0xe0 0xfc 0x11 0x00 0x00.

hwDhcpUserServerIpAddress.name: hwDhcpUserServerIpAddress
hwDhcpUserServerIpAddress.description: Indicates the IP address of the DHCP server to which the DHCP user belongs, in dotted decimal notation, for example, 10.11.104.10.

hwDhcpUserLeaseTime.name: hwDhcpUserLeaseTime
hwDhcpUserLeaseTime.description: Indicates the lease time of the DHCP user. Unit: second

hwDhcpUserRowStatus.name: hwDhcpUserRowStatus
hwDhcpUserRowStatus.description: Indicates the row status, used to query and delete the DHCP proxy user. The set operation supports only destroy(6). During query, active(1) is fixedly returned for this leaf. Options: 1. active(1) -when this leaf is queried, the value is fixed to active(1). 2. destroy(6) -delete a DHCP proxy user

hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanTable.name: hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanTable
hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanTable.description: Describes the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group in the domain mode. It supports the query, create, modify, and delete operations. The indexes of this table are hwVlanIndex and hwDhcpDomainName. hwVlanIndex is imported from hwVlanMIBTable in HUAWEI-VLAN-MIB. hwDhcpDomainName is imported from hwDhcpDomainTable.

hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanEntry.name: hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanEntry
hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanEntry.description: Describes the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group in the domain mode. It supports the query, create, modify, and delete operations. The indexes of this entry are hwVlanIndex and hwDhcpDomainName. hwVlanIndex is imported from hwVlanMIBTable in HUAWEI-VLAN-MIB. hwDhcpDomainName is imported from hwDhcpDomainTable.

hwDhcpDomainServerInVlan.name: hwDhcpDomainServerInVlan
hwDhcpDomainServerInVlan.description: Indicates the ID of the DHCP. It uses hwDhcpGroupID in hwDhcpGroupTable. Range: 0C19

hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanRowStatus.name: hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanRowStatus
hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanRowStatus.description: Row status, used to configure the DHCP server group bound to a domain under a VLAN. Options: 1. active(1) -when this leaf is queried, the value is fixed to active(1). 2. createAndGo(4) -create a binding between a domain under a VLAN to a DHCP server group 3. destroy(6) -delete the binding between a domain under a VLAN to the DHCP server group To create the binding between a domain under a VLAN to a DHCP server group, specify the index and hwDhcpDomainServerInVlan, set hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanRowStatus to createAndGo(4), and perform the set operation. To modify the binding between a domain under a VLAN to a DHCP server group, specify the index and hwDhcpDomainServerInVlan and perform the set operation. To delete the binding between a domain under a VLAN to the DHCP server group, specify the index and hwDhcpDomainServerInVlan, set hwDhcpDomainServerInVlanRowStatus to destroy(6), and perform the set operation. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1).

hwDhcpMacServerInVlanTable.name: hwDhcpMacServerInVlanTable
hwDhcpMacServerInVlanTable.description: Describes the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group in the MAC-range mode. It supports the create, modify, delete, and query operations. The indexes of this table are hwVlanIndex and hwDhcpMacRangeName. hwVlanIndex is imported from hwVlanMIBTable in HUAWEI-VLAN-MIB. hwDhcpMacRangeName is imported from hwDhcpMacRangeTable.

hwDhcpMacServerInVlanEntry.name: hwDhcpMacServerInVlanEntry
hwDhcpMacServerInVlanEntry.description: Describes the binding between the VLAN interface and the DHCP server group in the MAC-range mode. It supports the create, modify, delete, and query operations. The indexes of this entry are hwVlanIndex and hwDhcpMacRangeName. hwVlanIndex is imported from hwVlanMIBTable in HUAWEI-VLAN-MIB. hwDhcpMacRangeName is imported from hwDhcpMacRangeTable.

hwDhcpMacServerInVlan.name: hwDhcpMacServerInVlan
hwDhcpMacServerInVlan.description: Indicates the ID of the DHCP. It uses hwDhcpGroupID in hwDhcpGroupTable. Range: 0C19

hwDhcpMacServerInVlanRowStatus.name: hwDhcpMacServerInVlanRowStatus
hwDhcpMacServerInVlanRowStatus.description: Row status, used to configure the gateway IP address to which the MAC-range is bound. Options: 1. active(1) -when this leaf is queried, the value is fixed to active(1). 2. createAndGo(4) -create the binding between the MAC-range and the gateway IP address 3. destroy(6) -delete the binding between the MAC-range and the gateway IP address To create the binding between the MAC-range and the gateway IP address, specify the index first. The index is in the format of VLAN ID+MAC-range character length+ASCII value of each character. For example, to configure the DHCP server group for MAC-range 'abc' under VLAN1, the index value is 1.3.97.98.99. Then, specify hwDhcpMacServerInVlan, set hwDhcpMacServerInVlanRowStatus to createAndGo(4), and perform the set operation. To modify the binding between the MAC-range and the gateway IP address, specify the index and hwDhcpMacServerInVlan and perform the set operation. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1). To delete the binding between the MAC-range and the gateway IP address, specify the index and hwDhcpMacServerInVlan, set hwDhcpMacServerInVlanRowStatus to destroy(6), and perform the set operation.

hwDhcpRelayInterfaceSrcip.name: hwDhcpRelayInterfaceSrcip
hwDhcpRelayInterfaceSrcip.description: Configures or queries the filling mode of the source IP address of the current DHCP-relay upstream packet. Options: 1. receive(1) -indicates that in the DHCP packet sent from the relay to the server, the source IP address is set to the IP address of the Rx interface (user-side interface). 2. send(2) -indicates that in the DHCP packet sent from the relay to the server, the source IP address is set to the IP address of the Tx interface (network-side interface). Default: receive(1)

hwDhcpRelayInterfaceRelayAgent.name: hwDhcpRelayInterfaceRelayAgent
hwDhcpRelayInterfaceRelayAgent.description: Configures or queries the filling mode of the GIADDR field of the current DHCP-relay upstream packet. Options: 1. receive(1) -indicates that in the DHCP packet sent from the DHCP relay to the server, the gateway IP address is set to the IP address of the Rx interface (user-side interface). 2. send(2) -indicates that in the DHCP packet sent from the DHCP relay to the server, the gateway IP address is set to the IP address of the Tx interface (network-side interface). Default: receive(1)

hwDhcpSmltTable.name: hwDhcpSmltTable
hwDhcpSmltTable.description: Used to start and stop the DHCP emulation test and query the DHCP emulation test result. The index of this table is hwDhcpSmltIndex.

hwDhcpSmltEntry.name: hwDhcpSmltEntry
hwDhcpSmltEntry.description: Used to start and stop the DHCP emulation test and query the DHCP emulation test result. The index of this entry is hwDhcpSmltIndex.

hwDhcpSmltIndex.name: hwDhcpSmltIndex
hwDhcpSmltIndex.description: Indicates the index of a simulation user. Range: 1-255 Currently, the system supports only one simulation user.

hwDhcpSmltServicePortId.name: hwDhcpSmltServicePortId
hwDhcpSmltServicePortId.description: Indicates the index of the service port. The service port index here is 1 greater than the service port index queried through the CLI.

hwDhcpSmltOption60.name: hwDhcpSmltOption60
hwDhcpSmltOption60.description: Indicates the DHCP option 60 field. If the DHCP option 60 is not configured, the default configuration of the L3 interface is adopted. A string of 0-32 characters is supported.

hwDhcpSmltOverTime.name: hwDhcpSmltOverTime
hwDhcpSmltOverTime.description: Indicates the simulation timeout time. Range: 5-60 Default: 5 Unit: second

hwDhcpSmltResult.name: hwDhcpSmltResult
hwDhcpSmltResult.description: Indicates the DHCP simulation result. 0: Indicates that the DHCP simulation is successful. 6921509: Indicates the DHCP simulation is being performed. 6921510: Indicates that the DHCP simulation fails due to timeout.

hwDhcpSmltStartTime.name: hwDhcpSmltStartTime
hwDhcpSmltStartTime.description: Indicates the start time of the DHCP simulation.

hwDhcpSmltEndTime.name: hwDhcpSmltEndTime
hwDhcpSmltEndTime.description: Indicates the end time of the DHCP simulation.

hwDhcpSmltUserIp.name: hwDhcpSmltUserIp
hwDhcpSmltUserIp.description: Indicates the IP address obtained by the DHCP client.

hwDhcpSmltSubNetMask.name: hwDhcpSmltSubNetMask
hwDhcpSmltSubNetMask.description: Indicates the subnet mask of the IP address obtained by the DHCP client.

hwDhcpSmltDhcpServerIp.name: hwDhcpSmltDhcpServerIp
hwDhcpSmltDhcpServerIp.description: Indicates the IP address of the DHCP server.

hwDhcpSmltDnsServerIp.name: hwDhcpSmltDnsServerIp
hwDhcpSmltDnsServerIp.description: Indicates the IP address of the primary DNS server.

hwDhcpSmltDnsServerName.name: hwDhcpSmltDnsServerName
hwDhcpSmltDnsServerName.description: Indicates the name of the DNS server.

hwDhcpSmltSecondaryDnsServerIp.name: hwDhcpSmltSecondaryDnsServerIp
hwDhcpSmltSecondaryDnsServerIp.description: Indicates the IP address of the secondary DNS server.

hwDhcpSmltGatewayIp.name: hwDhcpSmltGatewayIp
hwDhcpSmltGatewayIp.description: Indicates the IP address of the gateway.

hwDhcpSmltRowStatus.name: hwDhcpSmltRowStatus
hwDhcpSmltRowStatus.description: Indicates the row status, used for starting and stopping the DHCP simulation. Options: 1. active(1) -when this leaf is queried, the value is fixed to active(1). 2. createAndGo(4) -start the DHCP simulation 3. destroy(6) -stop the DHCP simulation To start the DHCP simulation, input the index of the service port, set hwDhcpSmltRowStatus to createAndGo(4), and perform the set operation. To stop the DHCP simulation, input the simulation index, set hwDhcpSmltRowStatus to destroy(6), and perform the set operation. During the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1).

hwDhcpClientSystemAutoConfigStatus.name: hwDhcpClientSystemAutoConfigStatus
hwDhcpClientSystemAutoConfigStatus.description: Set the system auto-config status Options: 1. enable(1) -indicates the system auto-config is enabled 2. disable(2) -indicates the system auto-config is disabled

hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsTable.name: hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsTable
hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsTable.description: Queries and resets the statistics of transmitted and received DHCP L3 relay packets. The index of this table is ifIndex, and the value of the index must be 0.

hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsEntry.name: hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsEntry
hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsEntry.description: Queries and resets the statistics of transmitted and received DHCP L3 relay packets. The index of this entry is ifIndex, and the value of the index must be 0.

hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveUntrust.name: hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveUntrust
hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveUntrust.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP packets containing the untrust option 82 information.

hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveOverLength.name: hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveOverLength
hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveOverLength.description: Indicates the total number of DHCP packets that exceeds the maximum packet length after the option 82 information is added.

hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveOverMaxMessagesSi.name: hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveOverMaxMessagesSize
hwDhcpL3Option82ReceiveOverMaxMessagesSi.description: Indicates the total number of DHCP packets that exceeds the maximum option 82 length after the option 82 information is added.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveOffer.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveOffer
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveOffer.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP offer packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveAck.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveAck
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveAck.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP ACK packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveNak.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveNak
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveNak.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP NAK packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveDecline.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveDecline
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveDecline.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP decline packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveDiscover.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveDiscover
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveDiscover.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP discover packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveInform.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveInform
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveInform.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP inform packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveRelease.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveRelease
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveRelease.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP release packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveRequest.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveRequest
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveRequest.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP request packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveForceRenew.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveForceRenew
hwDhcpMessagesReceiveForceRenew.description: Indicates the total number of received DHCP FORCERENEW packets.

hwDhcpMessagesReceiveProxyPktAck.name: hwDhcpMessagesReceiveProxyPktAck

hwDhcpMACConflictNum.name: hwDhcpMACConflictNum
hwDhcpMACConflictNum.description: Indicates the total number of packets that have MAC address conflict.

hwDhcpSearchDownFailNum.name: hwDhcpSearchDownFailNum

hwDhcpUserNotZeroGiaddrPktNum.name: hwDhcpUserNotZeroGiaddrPktNum
hwDhcpUserNotZeroGiaddrPktNum.description: Indicates the total number of packets whose DHCP DISCOVER and REQUEST 'giaddr' are not zero on the user side.

hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsClear.name: hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsClear
hwDhcpMessagesStatisticsClear.description: Resets the DHCP packet statistics. Options: 1. clear(1) -resets the DHCP packet statistics

hwDhcpSmltRequestID.name: hwDhcpSmltRequestID
hwDhcpSmltRequestID.description: The Request ID of DHCP simulation.

hwDhcpConfilctIpAddress.name: hwDhcpConfilctIpAddress
hwDhcpConfilctIpAddress.description: The conflicting IP address got by DHCP.

hwDhcpConfilctIpAddressMask.name: hwDhcpConfilctIpAddressMask
hwDhcpConfilctIpAddressMask.description: The sub net mask of the conflicting IP address got by DHCP.

hwDhcpFlowStatisticsTable.name: hwDhcpFlowStatisticsTable
hwDhcpFlowStatisticsTable.description: Queries and resets the statistics of dhcp packets on flow. The index of this table is hwDhcpFlowStatisticsIndex. Statistics for a maximum of 64 service ports are supported at the same time.

hwDhcpFlowStatisticsEntry.name: hwDhcpFlowStatisticsEntry

hwDhcpFlowStatisticsIndex.name: hwDhcpFlowStatisticsIndex

hwDhcpFlowStatisticsRowStatus.name: hwDhcpFlowStatisticsRowStatus
hwDhcpFlowStatisticsRowStatus.description: Indicates the row status, used for enabling and disabling the DHCP statistics on flow. hwDhcpFlowStatisticsSendRequest.description: Number of sent DHCP request packets.
